a:5:{s:2:"id";s:8:"18678418";s:4:"info";a:4:{s:6:"Title:";s:22:"modUser.changePassword";s:7:"Author:";s:15:"Shaun McCormick";s:16:"Last Changed by:";s:12:"Mark Hamstra";s:12:"Wiki Markup:";s:37:"[revolution20:modUser.changePassword]";}s:6:"parent";s:8:"18678416";s:6:"source";s:1042:"h2. modUser::changePassword

Changes the password of a user. It first matches the oldPassword you specify to the current password using modUser-&gt;paswordMatches($oldPassword), then sets the password and finally it invokes the [revolution20:OnUserChangePassword] event. Returns true if the password was changed, false if not.


h2. Syntax

API Doc: [http://api.modxcms.com/modx/modUser.html#changePassword]


{code}
boolean changePassword (string $newPassword, string $oldPassword)
{code}

h2. Example

Change the password of the user &#39;foobar&#39; from &#39;boo123&#39; to &#39;b33r4me&#39;

{code}
$user = $modx-&gt;getObject(&#39;modUser&#39;,array(&#39;username&#39; =&gt; &#39;foobar&#39;));
$user-&gt;changePassword(&#39;b33r4me&#39;, &#39;boo123&#39;);
{code}
Change the password of the user currently logged in from &#39;mypass&#39; to &#39;s3cur3d&#39;.

{code}
$modx-&gt;user-&gt;changePassword(&#39;s3cur3d&#39;,&#39;mypass&#39;);
{code}

h2. See Also

{contentbylabel:labels=user|showLabels=false|showSpace=false}

